<item>
            <title>[LANG-448] Lower Ascii Characters don&apos;t get encoded by Entities.java</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LANG-448</link>
                <project id="12310481" key="LANG">Commons Lang</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have an XML files which sometimes contain control characters like 0x0c, or 0x18. These aren&apos;t allowed to be directly in the file (the validator fails with invalid character), so they need to be escaped.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When using &quot;StringEscapeUtils.escapeXml(String str)&quot;, which in turn uses &quot;Entities.escape(Writer writer, String str)&quot;, these characters don&apos;t get escaped. Only characters above 0x7F get escaped.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I fixed this bug, and attached a patch.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;N/A&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
